      • setPayPalEnvironment

        public void setPayPalEnvironment(PayPalEnvironment payPalEnvironment)
        setPayPalEnvironment() used to set the PayPalEnvironment to run the SDK in. Merchant partners can run their app in LIVE (for release version) or SANDBOX (for internal test versions) environments. Pass in PayPalEnvironment.LIVE to set the current payPalEnvironment to LIVE Pass in PayPalEnvironment.SANDBOX to set the current payPalEnvironment to SANDBOX
        Parameters:
        payPalEnvironment - - PayPalEnvironment the app is being run in. ex; PayPalEnvironment.LIVE or PayPalEnvironment.SANDBOX

      • setPayPalRedirectURL

        public void setPayPalRedirectURL(java.lang.String url)
        setPayPalRedirectURL() used to set the redirect-url/uri that the merchant provided as part of creating their app on www.paypal.com. redirectUrl is a merchant provided url provided under 'Return Url' on the merchant's application page at www.developer.paypal.com. This is a way to return back to the app after we Log In the user from a ^Custom-Tab. This can either be a uri-scheme. ex: testapp://paypalpay or this can be a universal link. ex: https://testmerchant.com/thankyou NOTE: For more information on where to find or how to generate either one of the above please visit the official docs.
        Parameters:
        url - - String type of 'Return Url' set by the merchant on the merchant's application page at www.developer.paypal.com. NOTE: ^Custom Tab is a hybrid between a WebView and a Browser that gives a secure implementation while showing a more seamless experience. More information about Chrome's version of Custom tabs can be found here

      • setClientId

        public void setClientId(java.lang.String id)
        setClientId() used to set the client-id that the merchant received as part of creating their app on www.paypal.com. Client Id is a unique identification number that the merchant receives for their application. This can be found on merchant's application page. Ex: "AYjwfTHXOxSEAwpMN7iloeyZFPhK_8uAkwHMnwvcszOUJQhVUpdnpUOfWTCwBm0aRjXJ5bliU0AuSoUb" NOTE: For more information on where to find or how to get a client-id please visit the official docs.
        Parameters:
        id - - Client Id provided in merchant's application page.

      • setURLScheme

        public void setURLScheme(java.lang.String scheme)
        setURLScheme() used to set the merchant selected URL-scheme name for their app. This is used to get redirects back from redirects to the ^Custom Tab. Only the SCHEME of the customURL needs to be provided to this function. NOTE: The value of this can be any String that the merchant partners decide is unique for their app. Ex: If merchants have declared our PYPLInitiateCheckout activity in their AndroidManifest.xml like, The value to be passed is "testapp", since this is the value of the atrribute scheme in the data tad
        Parameters:
        scheme - - Scheme set for PYPLInitiateCheckout activity in the merchants AndroidManifest.xml NOTE: ^Custom Tab is a hybrid between a WebView and a Browser that gives a secure implementation while showing a more seamless experience. More information about Chrome's version of Custom tabs can be found here

      • setMerchantQueryParams

        public void setMerchantQueryParams(java.lang.String[] merchantURLQueryParams)
        setMerchantQueryParams() used to set additional params that the merchant wants to set for the checkout session. { These would normally be provided as queryParams to the checkout url. } Takes in an array of Strings in the form of "paramName=paramValue" For example if the merchant wants to finish the transaction in PayPal they can pass a "userAction" param with a value that equals "commit". Sample Usage: setMerchantQueryParams(["userAction=commit"]) NOTE: THESE VALUES ARE OPTIONAL.
        Parameters:
        merchantURLQueryParams - - Optional params that the merchant can add for additional functionality.

      • setWebOnlyMode

        public void setWebOnlyMode(boolean isWebOnlyMode)
        setWebOnlyMode() used to set if the merchant intends to show webOnly mode. { Non-native mode, takes the user to a PayPal CheckoutPage in a ^Custom Tab } Takes in a boolean value. The value is false by default. Sample usage: setWebOnlyMode(true)
        Parameters:
        isWebOnlyMode - NOTE: ^Custom Tab is a hybrid between a WebView and a Browser that gives a secure implementation while showing a more seamless experience. More information about Chrome's version of Custom tabs can be found here
